With the prolongation of life expectancy in Japan, cancer is increasing in the 
elderly. Several retrospective studies have shown that the frequency of 
toxicity, response to chemotherapy and overall survival are similar in elderly 
and younger patients with cancer with good performance status. However, because 
many investigators have arbitrarily excluded elderly patients from clinical 
